The White House will host an event on June 12 to kick-off the National Week of Making, which lasts from June 12 to June 18. This week is meant to celebrate and promote individuals who use new tools and techniques to launch businesses, learn STEM skills, and contribute to American manufacturing. The event will include announcements and progress updates on the President's call to action to create a "Nation of Makers," and will feature leaders in the Maker community, the private sector, and senior Obama Administration officials.